-- Baffinland, RIM, TransAtlantic: Canada Equity Market Preview
-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t
-- 2010-12-29T13:51:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-29/baffinland-iron-mines-rim-transatlantic-canada-equity-market-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Canadian trading .  Baffinland Iron Mines Corp.  (BIM CT): Nunavut Iron Ore
Acquisition Inc. said it has increased its offer to purchase 60
percent of the developer of iron ore deposits to C$1.40.
Baffinland is the target of a takeover battle between
ArcelorMittal and Nunavut.  International Minerals Corp.  (IMZ CT): The company, which
produces silver and gold in Peru, said it signed a definitive
agreement with Hochschild Mining Plc “to fast-track
production” at the jointly owned Inmaculada gold and silver
property in southeast Peru. Lima-based Hochschild will provide
100 percent of the initial $100 million of funding required to
develop the Inmaculada mine as part of the agreement.  Research In Motion Ltd.  (RIM CT): The BlackBerry maker may
need to re-engineer its BlackBerry PlayBook tablet computer, due
next year, to improve its battery life, according to Kaufman
Bros. analyst Shaw Wu. The PlayBook has a battery life of two to
four hours, compared with as long as 10 hours for Apple Inc.’s
iPad, according to Wu.  TransAtlantic Petroleum Corp.  (TNP CT): The crude oil and
natural gas explorer was granted nine oil exploration licenses
in Turkey for a period of four years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Nikolaj Gammeltoft  in New York at 
